main event: Two officers from the 65th Air Division Maintenance Group observed two unidentified flying objects over the island of Terceira, Azores on October 8, 1954.
interesting points: The objects were circular in shape and bright orange in color.
The objects appeared to glide at a steady speed of approximately 700 mph from east to west across the island.
The objects were under observation for approximately 10 minutes.
When last observed, the objects continued their westerly course out to sea.
Detailed visual observations and descriptions of the objects were obtained from both observers, but no sounds were heard during the sighting.
witnesses: two officers from the 65th Air Division Maintenance Group
